items.title: You Can Save $200 on Samsung’s Elite Gaming Monitor Today
items.description: This is one of the biggest, baddest screens you can game on, and it’s marked down to less than the smaller version.

items.title: Brendan Carr Isn't Going to Stop Until Someone Makes Him
items.description: In the wake of Jimmy Kimmel's suspension, experts say the FCC commissioner's conduct is flatly unconstitutional. They also expect him to keep going.

items.title: No One Knows What ‘Terminally Online’ Means Anymore
items.description: The memes and online footprint of Charlie Kirk shooting suspect Tyler Robinson don’t place him neatly in a box, though many are still trying.

items.title: Move Aside, Chatbots: AI Humanoids Are Here
items.description: Today on Uncanny Valley, we talk about why the AI industry is investing in the development of humanoid robots, and what that means for us non-robots.

items.title: Jensen Huang Wants You to Know He’s Getting a Lot Out of the ‘Fantastic’ Nvidia-Intel Deal
items.description: Nvidia is investing $5 billion in Intel. The news comes after the US government took a roughly 10 percent equity stake in the struggling chipmaker.
